a futures market in computer time.wan auction method is described for allocatingcomputer time that allows the price of computer time to fluctuate with the demand and the relative priorityof users to be controlled so that more important projects get better access.  this auction is free of theperiodic fluctuation in computer use often associated with monthly time allocation schemes.cacm june, sutherland, i. e..kcomputer scheduling, auction, time allocation, operating efficiency.c.ca jb february ,   : pm